## Accessibility

### S6848 / S1082 — Non-native interactive elements need keyboard support
Any non-`<button>` element with an `onClick` handler must also have `role`, `tabIndex`, and `onKeyDown`.

```tsx
// WRONG
<div onClick={() => select(item)}>...</div>

// CORRECT
<div
  role="button"
  tabIndex={0}
  onClick={() => select(item)}
  onKeyDown={e => { if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') select(item) }}
>...</div>
```

### S6853 — Associate form labels with controls
Every `<label>` must reference its control via `htmlFor` / `id`. For Radix `<Select>`, use `aria-labelledby`.

```tsx
// WRONG
<label>Level Name</label>
<Input value={form.name} ... />

// CORRECT
<label htmlFor="level-name-input">Level Name</label>
<Input id="level-name-input" value={form.name} ... />

// For Select (no native id support):
<label id="level-label">Level</label>
<Select aria-labelledby="level-label" ...>
```

### S6772 — Avoid ambiguous JSX text spacing
Do not leave punctuation (`.`, `,`) on its own line after a closing tag. Place it directly after the tag.

```tsx
// WRONG
<a href="/path">link text</a>
.

// CORRECT
<a href="/path">link text</a>.
```

