## TypeScript Patterns

### Select `onValueChange` — null coalescing required
The Radix `onValueChange` callback receives `string | null`. State setters typed as `(v: string) => void` will fail without coalescing.

```tsx
// WRONG — TS2322
<Select onValueChange={setFilterValue} />

// CORRECT
<Select onValueChange={v => setFilterValue(v ?? '')} />
```

### Array index access — non-null assertion only inside length checks
`arr[0]` is `T | undefined` with `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`. Use `!` only when the length is already verified.

```tsx
// WRONG — TS2532
const first = items[0].name

// CORRECT
if (items.length > 0) {
  const first = items[0]!.name
}
```

### Global number functions — use `Number.*`
ESLint `no-restricted-globals` bans the bare globals. Always prefix with `Number.`.

```ts
// WRONG
parseInt('42')
parseFloat('3.14')
isNaN(value)

// CORRECT
Number.parseInt('42')
Number.parseFloat('3.14')
Number.isNaN(value)
```

### Zod v4 — `.issues` not `.errors`
Zod v4 renamed `ZodError.errors` to `ZodError.issues`.

```ts
// WRONG — TS2339
parsed.error.errors[0]?.message

// CORRECT
parsed.error.issues[0]?.message
```

### Prisma `_count` — use the relation name, not the model name
The `_count` key must match the relation field name in the schema, not the related model name.

```ts
// Schema: Organization { users Profile[] }
// WRONG
_count: { select: { profiles: true } }

// CORRECT
_count: { select: { users: true } }
```

### Non-existent model fields — derive or remove
Never access fields that do not exist in the Prisma schema. Compute them from existing fields.

```ts
// LeaveBalance has: totalDays, usedDays, pendingDays
// WRONG
bal.balance    // does not exist
bal.allocated  // does not exist

// CORRECT
const balance = bal.totalDays - bal.usedDays - bal.pendingDays
const allocated = bal.totalDays
```

### `prefer-immediate-return` — return directly
Do not assign to a variable only to return it on the next line.

```ts
// WRONG
async function getData() {
  const result = await prisma.employee.findMany(...)
  return result
}

// CORRECT
async function getData() {
  return prisma.employee.findMany(...)
}
```

### `string | null` state setters
When a value can be `null`, always coerce before passing to a `(v: string) => void` setter.

```ts
// WRONG — TS2345
setSearch(value)  // value: string | null

// CORRECT
setSearch(value ?? '')
```

