## Security

### S2068 — No hard-coded passwords or secrets
Scripts must never contain literal passwords. Read from environment variables and fail fast if absent.

```ts
// WRONG
const password = 'Admin@2026!'

// CORRECT
const password = process.env.ADMIN_PASSWORD
if (!password) {
  console.error('Set ADMIN_PASSWORD env var to run this script.')
  process.exit(1)
}
```

### S7637 — Pin GitHub Actions to a full commit SHA
Never reference an action by branch name (`@master`, `@main`). Always pin to a 40-character SHA and add a version comment.

```yaml
# WRONG
uses: SonarSource/sonarcloud-github-action@master

# CORRECT
uses: SonarSource/sonarqube-scan-action@713881670b6b3676cda39549040e2d88c70d582e # v8.2.0
```

