## Cognitive Complexity

### sonarjs/cognitive-complexity — Keep functions under 15
When SonarQube reports cognitive complexity > 15:
- Extract sections into named helper functions at module scope.
- Extract React state + effects into a dedicated custom hook (`useXxx`).
- Replace stacked ternaries with `if/else` blocks.
- Move sub-components out of the parent render function.

```tsx
// WRONG — deeply nested logic inside the component
export function Page() {
  // 80 lines of interleaved state, effects, and helpers
}

// CORRECT — extract a custom hook
function usePage() {
  const [data, setData] = useState(...)
  useEffect(() => { ... }, [...])
  function handleSubmit() { ... }
  return { data, handleSubmit }
}
export function Page() {
  const { data, handleSubmit } = usePage()
  return <div>...</div>
}
```
